title: Yahoo Lifestyle
text: Youre likely mistaken that your plans must be practically perfect before you share them with the public. In fact, you might spend too much time worrying about non-existent problems today. However, you cant begin to manage or even anticipate the full range of possibilities before they actually appear in the real world. Unfortunately, your efforts could be wasted if you focus on imaginary obstacles. Luckily, responding to unexpected issues enables you to engage in the process of creation in a more fruitful and exciting manner. Author W. Somerset Maugham wrote, Perfection has one grave defect. It is apt to be dull. Get Your Complete Cosmic Profile
